From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 15:30:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: rk3576-generic: enable USB host, storage, and
 keyboard

Add the USB host stack so a maskrom-RAM u-boot can be driven on the box
itself with a USB keyboard and boot or flash from a USB mass-storage
stick, with no laptop and no serial console. USB_XHCI_HCD is the
load-bearing symbol: the dwc3-generic host driver calls xhci_register(),
so without an XHCI HCD there is no host, and it selects USB_HOST for us.
USB_KEYBOARD (+ DM_KEYBOARD) and CONSOLE_MUX let the keyboard join serial
as console input.

The USB 3.0 port (drd0) is forced to dr_mode = "host" in the generic
control DTB. u-boot has no runtime OTG role switch on these nodes -- with
the download gadget built, "otg" binds the gadget identically to
"peripheral", so only "host" reaches the xhci stack. The port stays
USB2/high-speed on the already-built inno-usb2 PHY (SuperSpeed would
additionally need the usbdp combo PHY). This build is therefore not
simultaneously a rockusb/ums device -- which is the intent: it is driven
on-device rather than from a host.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 arch/arm/dts/rk3576-generic-u-boot.dtsi | 15 +++++++++++++++
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig        |  7 +++++++
 2 files changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/dts/rk3576-generic-u-boot.dtsi b/arch/arm/dts/rk3576-generic-u-boot.dtsi
index 98edec7f..1380235c 100644
--- a/arch/arm/dts/rk3576-generic-u-boot.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/dts/rk3576-generic-u-boot.dtsi
@@ -23,3 +23,18 @@
 	vref-supply = <&vref_1v8>;
 	status = "okay";
 };
+
+/*
+ * Drive the USB 3.0 port (drd0) as a fixed USB host so a keyboard and a
+ * mass-storage stick work at the u-boot prompt. rk3576-generic.dts sets this
+ * controller to "peripheral" (the rockusb/ums gadget); overriding dr_mode here
+ * wins. u-boot has no runtime OTG role switch on these nodes -- "otg" would bind
+ * the gadget, so "host" must be stated explicitly. The port stays USB2/high-speed
+ * on the already-built inno-usb2 PHY (rk3576-generic.dts keeps phys =
+ * <&u2phy0_otg>); SuperSpeed would additionally need the usbdp combo PHY. Forcing
+ * host means this build is not simultaneously a rockusb/ums device -- that is the
+ * point: this variant is driven on-device, not from a laptop.
+ */
+&usb_drd0_dwc3 {
+	dr_mode = "host";
+};
diff --git a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
index 501b1951..94f6a84a 100644
--- a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
+++ b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@ CONFIG_CMD_GPT=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MISC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MMC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_ROCKUSB=y
+CONFIG_CMD_USB=y
 CONFIG_CMD_USB_MASS_STORAGE=y
 # CONFIG_CMD_SETEXPR is not set
 CONFIG_CMD_RNG=y
@@ -45,9 +46,15 @@ CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_SHIFT=2
 CONFIG_SYS_NS16550_MEM32=y
 CONFIG_SYSRESET_PSCI=y
 CONFIG_USB=y
+CONFIG_USB_XHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_USB_XHCI_DWC3=y
 CONFIG_USB_DWC3=y
 CONFIG_USB_DWC3_GENERIC=y
 CONFIG_USB_GADGET=y
 CONFIG_USB_GADGET_DOWNLOAD=y
 CONFIG_USB_FUNCTION_ROCKUSB=y
+CONFIG_USB_STORAGE=y
+CONFIG_USB_KEYBOARD=y
+CONFIG_DM_KEYBOARD=y
+CONFIG_CONSOLE_MUX=y
 CONFIG_ERRNO_STR=y
